workflow.name: Enrich Company Data from LinkedIn via Bright Data & Google Sheets
workflow.description:
This n8n workflow automates the enrichment of a company list by discovering and extracting each company‚Äôs official LinkedIn URL using Bright Data‚Äôs search capabilities and Google Gemini AI for HTML parsing and result interpretation.

![image.png](fileId:1451)

## Who is this template for?
This workflow is ideal for sales, business development, and data research professionals who need to collect official LinkedIn company profiles for multiple organizations, starting from a list of company names in Google Sheets. It‚Äôs especially useful for teams who want to automate sourcing LinkedIn URLs, enrich their prospect database, or validate company data at scale.

## How it works
**Manual Trigger:**
The workflow is started manually (useful for controlled batch runs and testing).
**Read Company Names:**
Company names are loaded from a specified Google Sheets table.
**Loop Over Each Company:**
Each company is processed one-by-one:
- A custom Google Search URL is generated for each name.
- A Bright Data Web Unlocker request is sent to fetch Google search results for ‚Äúsite:linkedin.com [company name]‚Äù.
- Parse LinkedIn Profile URL Using AI:
Google Gemini (or your specified LLM) analyzes the fetched search page and extracts the most likely official LinkedIn company profile.

**Result Handling:**
- If a profile is found, it‚Äôs stored in the results.
- If not, an empty result is created, but you can add custom logic (notifications, retries, etc.).

**Batch Data Enrichment:**
All found company URLs are bundled into a single request for further enrichment from a Bright Data dataset.
**Export:**
The workflow appends the final, structured data for each company to another sheet in your Google Sheets file.
## Setup instructions
**1. Replace API Keys:**
Insert your Bright Data API key in these nodes:
- Bright Data Web Request - Google Search for Company LinkedIn URL
- HTTP Request - Post API call to Bright Data
- Snapshot Progress
- HTTP Request - Getting data from Bright Data

**2. Connect Google Sheets:**
Set up your Google Sheets credentials and specify the sheet for reading input and writing output.

**3. Customize Output Structure:**
Adjust the Python code node (see sticky note in the template) if you want to include additional or fewer fields in your output.

**4. Adjust for Scale or Error Handling:**
- You can modify the logic for ‚Äúnot found‚Äù results (e.g., to notify a Slack channel or retry failed companies).

**5. Run the Workflow:**
Start manually, monitor the run, and check your Google Sheet for results.

## Customization guidance
**Change Input/Output Sheets:**
Update the sheet names or columns if your source/target spreadsheet has a different structure.

**Use Another AI Model:**
Replace the Google Gemini node with another LLM node if preferred.

**Integrate Alerts:**
Add Slack or email nodes to notify your team when a LinkedIn profile is not found or when the process is complete.

parameters.pythonCode:
cleaned = []
for item in items:
  if not item.get("json"):
      raise ValueError("Missing input data on one of the inputs.")
    
  company = item.get("json")
  
  cleaned.append({
    "brightdata_name": company.get("name"),
    "country": company.get("country_code"),
    "linkedin_employees": company.get("employees_in_linkedin"),
    "about": company.get("about"),
    "description": company.get("description"),
    "additional_info": company.get("additional_information"),
    "specialties": company.get("specialties"),
    "company_size": company.get("company_size"),
    "type": company.get("organization_type"),
    "industries": company.get("industries"),
    "founded": company.get("founded"),
    "headquarters": company.get("headquarters"),
    "funding": company.get("funding"),
    "stock_info": company.get("stock_info"),
    "url": company.get("url"),
    "website": company.get("website"),
    "crunchbase_url": company.get("crunchbase_url"),
    
  })

return [{ "json": company } for company in cleaned]

nodes.name: Code - Prepare Request Body for Bright Data

parameters.content:
## Customization of the output data
You can modify the JSON keys in the code to include only the fields you want or add any additional. The current structure is a sample template.

## Each Company is Processed Individually
Every company name from the Google Sheets column is processed in a separate loop.

For each company:
- A unique Google search query is generated
- The search results are fetched using Bright Data API Request
- AI-powered parsing extracts the official LinkedIn profile
- This ensures accurate and dedicated extracting the LinkedIn URL for each company in the list.

## After Loop Completion 
After collecting all company URLs,
a single request body is prepared containing the list of companies.
This enables Bright Data to fetch and return dataset information for all companies in one batch request.

nodes.name: Bright Data Web Request - Google Search for Company LinkedIn URL

parameters.content:
## Why Add an Empty Result?
If a LinkedIn company profile is not found,
an empty result is added to the final output for that company.
This ensures all companies from the original list are represented in the results,
even if some were not found.
You can also implement custom logic here to handle ‚Äúnot found‚Äù cases differently -
for example, logging, sending notifications, or retrying the search.

## Replace YOUR_API_KEY
Replace "YOUR_API_KEY" with your Bright Data web_unlocker API key in these nodes:
**1.** Bright Data Web Request - Google Search for Company LinkedIn URL
**2.** HTTP Request- Post API call to Bright Data
**3.** Snapshot Progress
**4.** HTTP Request - Getting data from Bright Data

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
